The paper deals with the problem of simplifying Bayesian networks for probabilistic inference, which is a common task in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves statistical analysis and information theory, which suggests cs.LG and cs.IT as likely sub-categories. The empirical evaluation of the proposed method involves computational efficiency and performance, which aligns with cs.DS and cs.SI.
